fr.sii.ogham.sms.builder

Class SenderNumberBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.sii.ogham.core.fluent.AbstractParent<PhoneNumbersBuilder>
      • fr.sii.ogham.sms.builder.SenderNumberBuilder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Builder<PhoneNumberTranslator>, Parent<PhoneNumbersBuilder>

    public class SenderNumberBuilder
extends AbstractParent<PhoneNumbersBuilder>
implements Builder<PhoneNumberTranslator>
    Configures the sender phone number conversion (from a PhoneNumber to an AddressedPhoneNumber). The PhoneNumber is used by the developer to provide a simple phone number without knowing how phone number works (no need to handle formats, addressing, countries...). The AddressedPhoneNumber is used by Ogham implementations to have a phone number that is usable by a technical system.

      • convert

        public SenderNumberBuilder convert(PhoneNumberTranslator handler)
        Overrides the standard phone number conversions by the provided handler.

        If you call this method several times, only the last custom handler is used. If you need to apply several conversions, you can use CompositePhoneNumberTranslator implementation that delegates to PhoneNumberHandlers.

        Parameters:
        handler - the handler to use
        Returns:
        this instance for fluent chaining
